  "body": "- [ X ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\nI have some mock `.sol` contracts next to my JS tests in the `test/` folder.\r\nFrom the JS tests I import the contracts like this:\r\n```\r\nlet FooMock = artifacts.require('./mockcontracts/FooMock');\r\n```\r\nWhen I just simply run a ```truffle test --network test```, all is fine, but when I run e.g a ```truffle test ./test/exact_testfile.js --network test```, so I just select one testfile to run, I always get:\r\n```\r\nError: Could not find artifacts for ./mockcontracts/FooMock from any sources\r\n```\r\nIs there a way to solve this? If I move my mock contracts to the contracts/ folder, the individual tests work. But I would prefer to keep my mocks in the test/ folder.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nNot getting the `Could not find artifacts` error. \r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Ubuntu 16.04\r\n* Ethereum client: ganache\r\n* Truffle version: v5.0.5\r\n* node version: v8.15.0\r\n* npm version: v6.8.0\r\n",
